# .secondbrainignore
# Gitignore-style patterns for the Personal Agentic Second Brain ingestion system (`sb ingest`).
#
# Purpose:
# - Consulted **before** DataZone assignment, chunking, embedding, or indexing.
# - Any matching path is **skipped entirely**: no metadata, no vectors, no zone, tombstone if previously ingested.
# - Primary defense against ingesting secrets, PII, large binaries, and work-confidential content.
# - Complements (does not replace) the repo's .gitignore.
# - Works with the secret scanner (see AGENTS.md §3).
#
# Syntax: standard .gitignore rules (**, *, ! negation, etc.).
# Location: root of notes corpus or project root (tool resolves relative to ingest root).
#
# References:
# - PRD v0.2 §6 (Incremental ingest: content-hash IDs, tombstone on delete, `.secondbrainignore`)
# - PRD §10 (Threat model: Ingested secrets → Secret scanner + .secondbrainignore)
# - docs/data-zones.md (Interaction section: consulted before zone + chunking)
# - AGENTS.md §3 (Never commit list, DataZone rules, secret scanner)
#
# Recommendations:
# - Keep this file in version control (it contains no secrets).
# - Use it to carve out sub-paths inside PERSONAL or WORK_ADJACENT zones.
# - Review periodically with `sb ingest --status` (future).

# === Secrets & Credentials (highest priority) ===
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/.env.local
**/*secret*
**/*credential*
**/*password*
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/id_rsa*
**/auth.json
**/credentials.json
**/*-private.*

# === Work-adjacent / Confidential subdirectories ===
# Use specific subpaths so sibling files in the same zone are still ingested.
work/**/legal/**
work/**/nda/**
work/**/confidential/**
work/**/hr/**
acme-project/secret-nda/**
falcon-project/internal-only/**

# === Personal exports & reflection artifacts (cross-ref .gitignore) ===
actions.md
actions/
*.export.md
*reflection*.md
triage-*.md

# === Large binaries, media, DBs, caches (avoid polluting index) ===
*.pdf
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif
*.mp4
*.mov
*.zip
*.tar.gz
*.sqlite
*.db
*.lancedb/**
chroma/**
**/.cache/**
**/__pycache__/**
**/.venv/**

# === Local-only eval (real queries, results) ===
eval/golden_queries.local.yaml
eval/golden_queries.private.yaml
eval/results/**

# === Temp / scratch / logs ===
**/*.tmp
**/*.log
**/tmp/**
**/scratch/**
**/drafts/**
**/*-wip.*

# === Example patterns for demo / PUBLIC_DEMO hygiene ===
# (Normally you wouldn't ignore demo/ content, but these show the style)
# demo/private-test-data/**

# === Advanced: size-based (if your ingest tool supports) ===
# *.[0-9]mb
# *.[0-9][0-9]mb

# Notes:
# - Patterns are relative to the notes root being ingested.
# - Use `!` negation sparingly and only for deliberate exceptions.
# - After editing, run a dry ingest and review skipped counts.
# - This file is public-safe and should be committed (unlike the actual ignored content).